<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-06-07T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-06-07T15:00:00-05:00" n="142" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d142">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">811.20 Defense (M) Portugal/1534:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Portugal</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Norweb</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-06-07T16:00:00-04:00">June
                                        7, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1645. This is an interim reply to your 1725, June 6. IPOC<note n="3" xml:id="d142fn1">Iberian Peninsular Operating Committee.</note>
                                is meeting immediately to expedite supply purchase arrangements.
                                Pending detailed examination of data, general understanding of
                                Department and FEA is that approach will be liberal one as outlined
                                in paragraph 5, our 132, January 17. We agree to extend period of
                                program and to arrange for supply of additional items such as
                                locomotives, if possible on supply grounds. Shipping question may
                                pose serious difficulties if it should come to fore, but we will
                                press strongly should action be necessary. Incidentally, 100 jeeps
                                will be aboard next Portuguese ship. Sent to Lisbon, repeated to
                                    London.<note n="4" xml:id="d142fn2">Repeated to London as No.
                                    4512.</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Stettinius</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>